      "question": "If the $n^{th}$ term of an Arithmetic Progression is given by $a_n = 5 - 3n$, then the common difference of the sequence is",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The $n^{th}$ term of the AP is given as $a_n = 5 - 3n$.",
          "Find the first term $a_1$ by substituting $n = 1$: $a_1 = 5 - 3(1) = 2$.",
          "Find the second term $a_2$ by substituting $n = 2$: $a_2 = 5 - 3(2) = -1$.",
          "The common difference $d$ is given by $a_2 - a_1$.",
          "Calculate $d = -1 - 2 = -3$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$a_n = 5 - 3n \\\\ a_1 = 5 - 3(1) = 2 \\\\ a_2 = 5 - 3(2) = -1 \\\\ d = a_2 - a_1 \\\\ d = -1 - 2 = -3$"
